(
<figureCitation id="D9DD2A5E012BFFBD1BBEFA0BFDEDFA1E" box="[458,528,1414,1435]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[169,200,932,951]" captionTargetBox="[336,788,195,901]" captionTargetId="figure-183@8.[335,789,194,911]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Female genitalia of Alyma ariasvillegasai (Illustration Nancy V. Arias). Scale bar ¼ 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5345229" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5345229/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Figs. 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="D9DD2A5E012BFFBD1868FA0BFDD7FA1E" box="[540,554,1414,1435]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="10.[169,208,950,969]" captionTargetBox="[211,915,196,926]" captionTargetId="figure-206@10.[208,916,194,929]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs. 6–13. Antenna of Alyma species. 6) A. pallipes; 7) A. ariasvillegasai; 8) A." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5345233" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5345233/files/figure.png" pageId="6">7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="D9DD2A5E012BFFBD1842FA0BFDADFA1E" box="[566,592,1414,1435]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="11.[197,236,916,935]" captionTargetBox="[293,886,195,893]" captionTargetId="figure-202@11.[293,886,194,894]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs. 14–21. Pronotal hypomera of Alyma species. 14) A. pallipes; 15) A. ariasvillegasai; 16) A. calafquenensis; 17) A. contulmoensis; 18) A. lawlerae; 19) A. quiriquinaensis; 20) A." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5345235" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5345235/files/figure.png" pageId="6">15</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="D9DD2A5E012BFFBD1828FA0BFD8BFA1E" box="[604,630,1414,1435]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="12.[169,208,833,852]" captionTargetBox="[148,979,195,810]" captionTargetId="figure-203@12.[148,980,194,811]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs. 22–28. Tarsi of Alyma species. 22) A. pallipes; 23) A. ariasvillegasai; 24) A." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5345237" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5345237/files/figure.png" pageId="6">23</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="D9DD2A5E012BFFBD18F5FA0BFD67FA1E" box="[641,666,1414,1435]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[169,200,776,795]" captionTargetBox="[151,980,195,754]" captionTargetId="figure-235@14.[148,980,194,755]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 34. Distribution map of Alyma species. Alyma pallipes (Solier) (N), A. ariasvillegasai" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5345243" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5345243/files/figure.png" pageId="6">34</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="415936DB012BFFBD1ADDFA22FC2FFA47" blockId="6.[148,978,1455,1570]" box="[169,978,1455,1474]" pageId="6">
<emphasis id="7392EAC9012BFFBD1ADDFA22FEEAFA47" bold="true" box="[169,279,1455,1474]" pageId="6">Description.</emphasis>
Body: Elongate; brown; integument shiny; vestiture yellowish pale, decumbent,
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="415936DB012BFFBD1AE0FA4AFD5DFA5F" blockId="6.[148,978,1455,1570]" box="[148,672,1479,1498]" pageId="6">
sides parallel-sided; length 
<quantity id="861E9B3E012BFFBD1B0BFA4AFE3EFA5F" box="[383,451,1479,1498]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.3" pageId="6" unit="mm" value="6.3">6.3 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity id="861E9B3E012BFFBD1870FA4AFDB4FA5F" box="[516,585,1479,1498]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="6" unit="mm" value="1.9">1.9 mm</quantity>
; PEI: 2.6.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="415936DB012BFFBD1AD8FA52FC2CFA77" blockId="6.[148,978,1455,1570]" box="[172,977,1503,1522]" pageId="6">
<emphasis id="7392EAC9012BFFBD1AD8FA52FF27FA77" box="[172,218,1503,1522]" italics="true" pageId="6">Head</emphasis>
: convex; frontoclypeal carina region extended forward; clypeus and labrum with setae
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="415936DB012BFFBD1AE0FA7AFC2FF98F" blockId="6.[148,978,1455,1570]" box="[148,978,1526,1546]" pageId="6">
semi-decumbent; labrum slightly convex, 2 
<emphasis id="7392EAC9012BFFBD1878FA7BFDE3F98C" bold="true" box="[524,542,1526,1545]" pageId="6">3</emphasis>
as long as wide; antennomera 2 through 8 serrate,
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="415936DB012BFFBD1AE0F982FC2DF9A7" blockId="6.[148,978,1455,1570]" box="[148,976,1551,1570]" pageId="6">
antennomere 9 exceeding pronotal posterior angles, [AP: 7-6-10-10-11-13-12-9-10-12], (
<figureCitation id="D9DD2A5E012BFFBD19FBF982FC39F9A7" box="[911,964,1551,1570]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="10.[169,208,950,969]" captionTargetBox="[211,915,196,926]" captionTargetId="figure-206@10.[208,916,194,929]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs. 6–13. Antenna of Alyma species. 6) A. pallipes; 7) A. ariasvillegasai; 8) A." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5345233" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5345233/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="415936DB012BFFBD1A6FF901FD05F91B" blockId="6.[27,784,1676,1713]" box="[27,760,1676,1694]" pageId="6">
Downloaded From: https://bioone.org/journals/The-Coleopterists-Bulletin on 
<date id="3558101B012BFFBD18FBF901FD05F91B" box="[655,760,1676,1694]" pageId="6" value="2021-08-26">26 Aug 2021</date>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="415936DB012BFFBD1A6FF92DFCEDF935" blockId="6.[27,784,1676,1713]" box="[27,784,1695,1713]" pageId="6">Terms of Use: https://bioone.org/terms-of-use Access provided by The Coleopterists Society</paragraph>
<caption id="15996653012AFFBC1AB1FD6DFCFBFD71" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5345227" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5345227" box="[197,774,736,756]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5345227/files/figure.png" pageId="7" startId="7.[197,228,736,755]" targetBox="[181,998,194,715]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph id="415936DB012AFFBC1AB1FD6DFCFBFD71" blockId="7.[197,774,736,756]" box="[197,774,736,756]" pageId="7">
<emphasis id="7392EAC9012AFFBC1AB1FD6DFF03FD76" bold="true" box="[197,254,736,755]" pageId="7">Fig. 3.</emphasis>
Scanning electron micrograph of head of 
<taxonomicName id="86E64D58012AFFBC180FFD6CFCFCFD71" authorityName="Arias, new" authorityYear="2004" box="[635,769,737,756]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Alyma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lawlerae">
<emphasis id="7392EAC9012AFFBC180FFD6CFCFCFD71" box="[635,769,737,756]" italics="true" pageId="7">Alyma lawlerae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="415936DB012AFFBC1AB3FC99FD37FC02" blockId="7.[175,1007,788,1046]" pageId="7">
<emphasis id="7392EAC9012AFFBC1AB3FC99FEE0FCA2" box="[199,285,788,807]" italics="true" pageId="7">Prothorax</emphasis>
: convex medially; areolate, sides parallel; base curved; pronotal posterior angles straight; prosternal lobe bent; prosternum convex; pronotosternal lobe marginate broadly curved; pronotosternal suture sinuate; hypomeron punctate, sinuate basally, antennal groove present (
<figureCitation id="D9DD2A5E012AFFBC19BEFCC9FF3BFCEA" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="11.[197,236,916,935]" captionTargetBox="[293,886,195,893]" captionTargetId="figure-202@11.[293,886,194,894]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs. 14–21. Pronotal hypomera of Alyma species. 14) A. pallipes; 15) A. ariasvillegasai; 16) A. calafquenensis; 17) A. contulmoensis; 18) A. lawlerae; 19) A. quiriquinaensis; 20) A." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5345235" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5345235/files/figure.png" pageId="7">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
); prosternum at procoxae marginate, and slightly elevated; procoxal distance 2.0 
<emphasis id="7392EAC9012AFFBC19FFFCD6FC60FCEB" bold="true" box="[907,925,859,878]" pageId="7">3</emphasis>
procoxal diameter, pronotosternal spine length 0.7 
<emphasis id="7392EAC9012AFFBC1867FCFEFDD8FC03" bold="true" box="[531,549,883,902]" pageId="7">3</emphasis>
procoxal diameter.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="415936DB012AFFBC1AB3FC01FF02FC4A" blockId="7.[175,1007,788,1046]" pageId="7">
<taxonomicName id="86E64D58012AFFBC1AB3FC01FEE7FC1A" box="[199,282,908,927]" class="Trilobita" family="Styginidae" genus="Scutellum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Corynexochida" pageId="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7392EAC9012AFFBC1AB3FC01FEE7FC1A" box="[199,282,908,927]" italics="true" pageId="7">Scutellum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: U-shaped, vestiture semi-decumbent, long, yellow; mesocoxae separated by 0.3 
<emphasis id="7392EAC9012AFFBC19A9FC06FC12FC1B" bold="true" box="[989,1007,907,926]" pageId="7">3</emphasis>
mesocoxal diameter; posterior margin of mesosternal cavity extending posteriorly 0.4 
<emphasis id="7392EAC9012AFFBC190AFC2EFC6DFC33" bold="true" box="[894,912,931,950]" pageId="7">3</emphasis>
mesocoxal diameter.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="415936DB012AFFBC1AB3FC59FDCBFB93" blockId="7.[175,1007,788,1046]" pageId="7">
<emphasis id="7392EAC9012AFFBC1AB3FC59FF06FC62" box="[199,251,980,999]" italics="true" pageId="7">Elytra</emphasis>
: interstria rugulose, slightly convex; striae pitted, pits regular; interstria convex; elytral apex rounded and explanate. 
<emphasis id="7392EAC9012AFFBC1BCDFC66FE24FC7B" box="[441,473,1003,1022]" italics="true" pageId="7">Leg</emphasis>
: yellowish brown; tarsomere 4 almost similar in length to tarsomere 1, [TP: 25-19-18-23-15], (
<figureCitation id="D9DD2A5E012AFFBC1B9EFB8EFDD6FB93" box="[490,555,1027,1046]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="12.[169,208,833,852]" captionTargetBox="[148,979,195,810]" captionTargetId="figure-203@12.[148,980,194,811]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs. 22–28. Tarsi of Alyma species. 22) A. pallipes; 23) A. ariasvillegasai; 24) A." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5345237" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5345237/files/figure.png" pageId="7">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
